column1: I began to feel a little run down yesterday so I took a COVID-19 test. Last night the results came back positive for the virus. My symptoms remain mild and I am following CDC guidelines. I am quarantining and will continue to serve the people of Central Washington from home.

The @ChelanDouglasHD has been working to protect individuals & families throughout NCW. In East Wenatchee we discussed their important focus on getting COVID-19 safety info to Hispanic & agricultural communities. https://t.co/cjevcBfrUf

Last week I hosted a meeting with Benton Franklin & Walla Walla County officials to discuss current and upcoming healthcare needs as we continue to combat the COVID-19 pandemic.   More from @kimatv: https://t.co/WZDwGcISrV

And that’s a wrap! Thank you to all of the business owners who opened their doors to me & shared how they are working to support the community of Connell through the COVID-19 pandemic and beyond. #ConnellMainStreetTour
For decades the Connell Small Mall has been bringing local vendors together in one place. Business snapped back when COVID-19 restrictions were lifted. #ConnellMainStreetTour https://t.co/Z6R54XxTpB

Down to rural Franklin County where I met with City of Connell officials to learn how they are applying state COVID-19 regulations to their targeted local response. Thank you for your hard work keeping the community of Connell safe & healthy! https://t.co/a58qTmCDA6

I am starting today meeting with the Adams County Health Department & local healthcare officials at @CBHA_WA. I am encouraged by their dedication to working with schools businesses & local government to develop a comprehensive COVID-19 recovery strategy + fight pandemic fatigue. https://t.co/F95L6HmWEC
Now for the #QuincyMainStreetTour! I am touring around Quincy to learn about new & developing projects and hear firsthand about COVID-19 impacts on our local economy.

We discussed the impacts COVID-19 & the recent wildfires have had on our agriculture industry + ongoing conservation projects. I am grateful for the support of @BillAtUSDA & his team for helping #WA04 farmers & ranchers through these difficult times.
BREAKING NEWS: @SecretarySonny announced a second round of COVID-19 relief from @USDA that will benefit our agriculture industry in #WA04.   https://t.co/wsPqpmJMR3

Today is #SuicidePrevention Day. Even before COVID-19 we saw an unfortunate spike in rates of mental health issues across the country. The loneliness & anxiety brought on by prolonged isolation +  financial pressures of extended economic shutdowns may be overwhelming. #WSPD2020 https://t.co/6r4iserhW5

I enjoyed the opportunity to update you on my work in Congress + answer your questions about the future of a COVID-19 vaccine the benefits of commercial nuclear energy development & how our communities can work together with law enforcement to create a more just equal society.

Did you know the Paycheck Protection Program helped saved over 50 million jobs since the outbreak of the COVID-19 pandemic? This vital assistance program ended on August 8 but the needs of the small and locally owned businesses that power our economy did not. https://t.co/lKaWWgh2sq

This week I joined my colleagues in sending a letter to @USDA @SecretarySonny urging the inclusion of American wheat growers in upcoming COVID-19 aid packages. Read the letter on my website 👇👇   https://t.co/C7rPWkw8br

Did you know Central Washington has the 4⃣th highest number of organic producers in the United States? The organic agriculture sector is growing across the country and - like all producers - organic growers are negatively impacted by the COVID-19 pandemic.
The expansion of telemedicine may be a silver lining of the dark cloud that is the COVID-19 pandemic.
The COVID-19 pandemic has shed light on the reality that fast reliable internet access is no longer a luxury but a necessity.

Great to be with @awbolympia today at their Federal Affairs Summit to discuss expanding rural broadband access and steps Central Washington Businesses are taking to help develop a COVID-19 vaccine. https://t.co/gpOxwtQgtL

I have been working to enhance these services through legislation like the Increasing Rural Health Access During the COVID-19 Public Health Emergency Act & this Executive Order will continue to strengthen our ability to care for patients of all ages and all walks of life.

Yesterday President @realDonaldTrump signed an Executive Order to ensure patients in rural communities like ours can continue to access telehealth services beyond the COVID-19 pandemic.  https://t.co/6X7FMF0koj

I led a bipartisan letter with @RepDeanPhillips to urge House leadership to help small businesses maximize their PPP dollars by including legislation like my bill the FIRST Act in the next COVID-19 relief package.  Read more ⬇️ https://t.co/LxFpVcxide

I joined @komonews for their Connect to Congress segment to provide an update on the #WA04 COVID-19 response and several other issues from the reopening of schools in the fall to the importance of water infrastructure to our rural communities.  https://t.co/8SXk19c4Jw

Don't forget! Taxes are due tomorrow. The IRS extended the tax filing deadline to July 15 to accommodate those affected by COVID-19.  If you have questions or need assistance with the IRS my office can help. Contact my Yakima office at (509) 452-3243.   https://t.co/2UK05f8iSx

ICYMI: @SecretarySonny made adjustments to the Coronavirus Food Assistance Program that will offer relief to specialty crop growers in our state and across the country.  Washington's farmers and ranchers can apply for the Coronavirus Food Assistance Program until August 28. https://t.co/nnvktlBmRQ
This week @SecretarySonny revised the #CFAP to ensure more of WA's specialty crop producers have access to the COVID-19 relief program!   https://t.co/EQ4GFKpCjZ
Apples potatoes and several other Washington-grown products have been added to list of the eligible commodities for the Coronavirus Food Assistance Program!  https://t.co/Mqlo1ayLr0

Due to internal changes made to combat COVID-19 people in #WA04 have experienced significant delays in contacting the IRS. Zachary from Richland contacted my office for assistance and after working with my staff he successfully received his refund in the amount of $11510.

I joined @RepBrindisi & @RepStefanik in leading a bipartisan letter to call on USDA to use COVID-19 relief funding to help apple growers across the country.   Learn more and read the letter: https://t.co/Y8i1yOYWH7
Expanding telehealth can help rural healthcare providers continue to care for patients in communities throughout #WA04 during a pandemic like COVID-19 & beyond.

I was proud to support the Families First Coronavirus Response Act which authorized the Pandemic-EBT program. P-EBT aims to provide assistance to families of children who are eligible for free & reduced meals through school closures related to COVID-19.  https://t.co/6j4RSsz2Iw

As the coronavirus has exposed and as food-insecure Americans now better understand: There is too much at stake.  The Farm Workforce Modernization Act which is awaiting action in the Senate is the first step.

Today I joined the Alliance to discuss how many of the issues facing our country - from rural broadband access to international trade - are affecting businesses employers & workers in #WA04 + how we can work together to help our district swiftly & safely recover from COVID-19.

The newest jobs numbers demonstrate that America is finally getting back to work. We must continue to prevent the spread of COVID-19 in #WA04 & across the country but it is encouraging to see businesses reopening with safety measures & precautions.   https://t.co/HpG0QctTgy

Hanford workers & other local orgs are donating time and money to support ongoing COVID-19 relief efforts. Take a moment to read about some of the efforts in #WA04 to bolster food bank delivery healthcare access & more during these unprecedented times.  https://t.co/GYcLut1Gxa

I agree with the @Yakima_Herald. As Congress continues to discuss COVID-19 relief efforts I will continue to advocate for our community health centers and the more than 100000 of patients who rely on them in #WA04.  https://t.co/phcsll5UAO
The Coronavirus Food Assistance Program (CFAP) is open for applications TODAY.  Find more details and watch the webinar here: https://t.co/BGiLRVtWYq

Last week I participated in a webinar hosted by @awbolympia alongside @cathymcmorris & Jon Wyss of @USDA. We discussed COVID-19's impact on our state's agriculture industry & the federal program aiming to provide relief to farmers and ranchers.

Bad actors across the state are taking advantage of the COVID-19 pandemic to prey on those seeking unemployment. Find out how you can protect yourself and your loved ones from these attacks.   https://t.co/94nwL2azsY

The federal government is working to ensure WA healthcare workers first responders & other heroes on the frontlines of COVID-19 have the PPE they need. As we move toward a safe reopening I will continue to advocate for ensuring our #WA04 communities are well-equipped. https://t.co/kjd43b770W
President Trump has initiated Operation Warp Speed a national program that aims to develop a vaccine for COVID-19 by January 2021.   https://t.co/vtNfBDheNP

Tomorrow @cathymcmorris Jon Wyss with @USDA and I will join @awbolympia for a discussion about our agriculture industry's response to COVID-19 & how we can continue to support our farmers and ranchers to ensure a strong food supply. https://t.co/iMOe6oE0yo

The Coronavirus Food Assistance Program aims to provide direct relief to farmers & ranchers so they can continue to produce food throughout this pandemic & into the future.  @USDA is hosting a webinar tomorrow to help producers apply for this aid: https://t.co/VK5aNexLap

During the COVID-19 outbreak access to Internet and rural broadband is more important than ever. Wi-Fi hotspots are being offered across our district for free so students and families can continue to work and learn remotely.  https://t.co/5VPxzoC3tz

As discussions for an infrastructure package continue we recognize @usbr water projects play an important role in our communities across the West. @RepJimCosta & I led a bipartisan letter urging inclusion of water infrastructure in an upcoming COVID-19 relief package. https://t.co/3qvduS8MWu

Unfortunately scammers are using the COVID-19 pandemic to try to steal Medicare Numbers personal information and money.   Learn how to protect yourself or your loved ones from Medicare fraud: https://t.co/cXrKJRFVDs

The public meeting I had planned to get feedback from local community members has been postponed due to the coronavirus outbreak but I will continue to urge Congress to pass this important legislation and take steps to end the MMIW crisis.  #MMIW #MMIWActionNow #EndMMIW

.@POTUS & @SecretarySonny are prioritizing America's farmers & ranchers by providing relief throughout the COVID-19 outbreak. In Congress I am working with the Administration to ensure aid for producers is commensurate with their damages.   Read more: https://t.co/EZKQiM8yQ7
I am working in Congress and with the Administration to ensure that the impact of COVID-19 is not a lasting one. Read more: https://t.co/xdgMewz9cm

Throughout the COVID-19 outbreak our ag industry continues to produce the food we need to feed our families but farmers & ranchers - particularly specialty crop producers in #WA04 - are facing dire situations. https://t.co/sTuwoR7481
Learn more about what @PNNLab is doing to combat the COVID-19 pandemic: https://t.co/aGx9qiqqlR

THANK YOU to the scientists & researchers working at our National Labs across the country to keep America running protect our national security and develop ways to prevent & treat COVID-19. A special thank you to @PNNLab right here in #WA04! https://t.co/Qa6F4wTfTn

Any decision that alters the way we do business in the House of Representatives must be bipartisan. I am glad @GOPLeader @TomColeOK04 & @RodneyDavis will have an opportunity to craft the proposal for congressional voting during the COVID19 outbreak.  https://t.co/vylycxLwXu

A special thank you to today #ToThoseWhoKeepUsMoving throughout the coronavirus outbreak. Whether it be by truck train or barge - our supply chain depends on reliable transportation.   @TransportGOP @TransportDems https://t.co/wSsGaT3uVN

For your morning read my column in the Sunnyside Sun details why rural hospitals are in need of additional support throughout our response to the COVID-19 outbreak and what I am doing in Congress to help:   https://t.co/wiXI9KQMTa

As we observe #NationalParkWeek I encourage you and your family to celebrate our nation's beautiful public lands and parks. While some of these sites have been closed to help prevent the spread of COVID-19 you can still explore them from the comfort of your own home.

Based on the guidance of public health officials we have made – and will continue to make – necessary changes to our operations that attempt to keep America’s public lands accessible during this pandemic allowing the public to have a place to be socially distant together.
A great piece by @Interior Secretary Bernhardt on how the agency is working to maintain public access to our public lands throughout the COVID-19 pandemic:  https://t.co/xVgyi8cxZu

Today homebuilders across the country are participating in @NAHBhome's #COVID19SafetyStandDown to pause work & review safety guidelines for their job sites. The construction sector & its workers will help lead the U.S. toward economic recovery - while prioritizing safety.
The PPP was designed to keep businesses afloat throughout the COVID-19 pandemic and I will continue working to ensure these crucial providers can continue to care for those in need.

Listen live at 3:30 PST on @610KONARADIO to hear about our #HousingIsEssential efforts + the federal response to COVID-19 and how it is affecting other industries important in #WA04 like agriculture: https://t.co/Wm9AxSCrWq https://t.co/qakOzRGcKW

Regardless of @GovInslee's decision I believe construction workers & homebuilders will be leading our nation's industries - with safety at the forefront - back into economic greatness as we recover from COVID-19. #HousingIsEssential

Seniors in #WA04 receiving Social Security payments will NOT have to file a tax return to receive the COVID-19 economic impact statement. Per the Dept. of the Treasury payments will be automatically deposited in eligible accounts: https://t.co/uHRKt1KVOa

I am in D.C. preparing to vote for the third coronavirus relief package the CARES Act. This is an unprecedented bill for unprecedented times but I am proud to have worked to include priorities for rural communities like ours in Central Washington. https://t.co/1CoAcYChQe

If you or a loved one receive notice that your benefits are being discontinued because of Social Security office closures or because of the Coronavirus this is a SCAM. Find out how to protect yourself here: https://t.co/RLzB93C7JZ

SCAM ALERT: The Social Security Administration is NOT suspending or discontinuing benefits because of the COVID-19 outbreak. Many Social Security offices are closed to in-person visitors but employees are still hard at work.

Our region is rich with specialty crops & farmers in #WA04 provide nutritious food to families & nutrition programs across the country. @RepJimmyPanetta @RepFredUpton and I led a letter requesting support for our specialty crop producers during the COVID-19 outbreak.
Learn why social distancing is so important to not only protect yourself but to protect those who are most vulnerable during the COVID-19 outbreak. https://t.co/LSBS1a2vsV

Food security is national security. We must ensure our farmers and ranchers - who continue to work hard through the COVID-19 outbreak to keep food on grocery store shelves & on our tables - have access to a legal workforce.

Our national labs have the capability to make a real positive impact when it comes to preventing the spread of COVID-19 & other potential viruses. We are fortunate to have the scientists & resources of @PNNLab in #WA04 as they work to improve & expand screening and testing. https://t.co/eIWcooxg4r

The scientists & researchers at @PNNLab are working diligently to help the U.S. respond to the COVID-19 outbreak. Today I toured the lab alongside @sharonbrownWA @BradKlippert @RepBoehnke to learn about the Lab's efforts to fight the spread of this virus. https://t.co/Qf8tNtNE3r

The emergency supplemental funding bill passed by Congress authorized the @SBAgov to offer disaster loans to small business owners to pay fixed debts payroll accounts payable & other expenses that can't be paid due to the COVID-19 outbreak.   More info:  https://t.co/oAuMKYuWuK
I just voted to support the Families First Coronavirus Response Act: https://t.co/fxOa9f10Ds

As the #Coronavirus response changes day-to-day there are several steps you can take to stay informed and keep you and your loved ones healthy. Visit my website for a list of resources for Central Washington families individuals and businesses: https://t.co/85tViRGDHT

WA is at the epicenter of the #Coronavirus outbreak in the US. I was proud to join @VP Pence + our bipartisan congressional delegation to meet with @GovInslee & discuss how we can work together to protect the health of people across the country. https://t.co/9AWI8oaQcJ

Today I am traveling to WA with @VP & my bipartisan colleagues to meet with @GovInslee tour the emergency operations center & ensure our state has the federal support we need to respond to COVID-19. I am proud to work across the aisle to protect Americans & the people of #WA04.

Yesterday I voted to support an emergency funding package to tackle #Coronavirus at home & abroad including resources for state & local health departments and expedited vaccine development. https://t.co/vDXbZ2DDj1

In #WA04 the world-class scientists at @PNNLab are conducting critical research to develop methods to prepare for and respond to infectious diseases and threats like COVID-19. Read more in the @TriCityHerald:  https://t.co/nFNNn2wFZZ
Protecting Americans and developing a vaccine for COVID-19 should not partisan or political. Thank you @Mike_Pence for your leadership on the Coronavirus Task Force. https://t.co/1NOyFYXgr6
